x4freetext: neutron time of flight spectrometer was used to
measure the neutron angular distributions in the range
of 10 to 150 degrees with respect to the incident beam
.flight path = 7 to 9 m with a neutron energy
.absolute detection efficiency was performed at the
Los Alamos, using D(t,n)4He and D(d,n)3He reactions.
.proton recoil telescope was used at 0 degree.

x4freetext: uncertainties relative to other points in
the angular distribution are given.  these include only
theuncertainty in peak area and the estimated
uncertainty in the corrections for neutron attenuation
.in the nuclei above mass 90 only transitions to
isobaric analogue state of the target nuclei were
data taken from the thesis by R.F.Bentley,
